<Base title="Experience" description="Career history, certifications, and education.">
  <h1>Experience</h1>
  <p class="muted">
    {site.yearsExperience} years across cloud, infrastructure, and data platform operations &mdash;
    including {site.yearsAtMicrosoft} years at Microsoft.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Microsoft &mdash; Senior Manager, Platform Reliability &amp; Operations (Data Platforms)</h2>
    <p class="muted">Sep 2022 – Present · Redmond, WA</p>
    <p>
      Lead infrastructure, reliability, security, and operations for Microsoft's Cloud Marketing Data Platform, a
      business-critical platform supporting global marketing and customer-lifecycle workloads.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Lead a <strong>40–45 person global team</strong> across infrastructure engineering, data operations, and program management, accountable for 24×7 platform reliability and operational readiness.</li>
      <li>Own platform reliability, security compliance, business continuity, and cost optimization for Azure-based data platforms built on <strong>Synapse, Cosmos DB, Fabric</strong>, and enterprise cloud services.</li>
      <li>Drove platform optimization and modernization initiatives that reduced operational complexity and delivered <strong>$1M+ in cost savings</strong> through capacity optimization, automation, and elimination of inefficiencies.</li>
      <li>Improved platform stability and predictability by strengthening monitoring, incident response, and standardized operational practices.</li>
      <li>Partner with engineering, privacy, security, and compliance teams to ensure platforms meet enterprise security, compliance, and data-governance standards.</li>
      <li>Established an operations model focused on risk reduction, disciplined execution, and continuous improvement as platform scale and business demand increased.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Microsoft &mdash; Senior Program Manager, Cloud Operations &amp; Continuous Improvement</h2>
    <p class="muted">Jan 2020 – Aug 2022 · Redmond, WA</p>
    <p>
      Led cloud operations and continuous improvement initiatives across Microsoft's cloud infrastructure ecosystem,
      with a focus on capacity readiness, cost discipline, and execution at scale.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Drove capacity and spares planning to support customer demand while maintaining strict cost controls and operational predictability.</li>
      <li>Delivered <strong>multi-million-dollar cost avoidance and savings</strong> through demand forecasting improvements, spares optimization, and elimination of inefficiencies.</li>
      <li>Led cross-functional Lean / Kaizen initiatives that reduced operational friction and improved end-to-end execution.</li>
      <li>Partnered with engineering, finance, and supply chain leadership to improve visibility into capacity, spend, and operational risk.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Microsoft &mdash; Senior Program Manager Lead, Cloud Operations &amp; Datacenter Reliability (CO+I)</h2>
    <p class="muted">Feb 2013 – Dec 2019 · Redmond, WA</p>
    <p>
      Led Azure Datacenter Critical Environment IT Infrastructure &mdash; accountable for the IT systems, tooling,
      security, and operations that underpin power, cooling, and instrumentation environments across Microsoft's
      global datacenter fleet.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Built and led a <strong>~60-person global organization</strong> responsible for 24×7 reliability, incident response, and operational readiness of mission-critical datacenter environments supporting thousands of production workloads.</li>
      <li>Established the <strong>first Azure Datacenter Instrumentation &amp; Pre-Production Lab</strong>, enabling safe testing of infrastructure changes before global rollout and significantly reducing operational risk.</li>
      <li>Drove virtualization and standardization of critical environment IT systems, improving scalability and delivering ~$1M in cost savings over two years.</li>
      <li>Strengthened security, monitoring, and compliance posture for datacenter critical environment systems as Azure scaled globally.</li>
      <li>Led cross-functional execution with datacenter engineering, facilities, and service teams to improve availability, incident response, and operational predictability.</li>
      <li>Initiated and sustained continuous improvement programs across the datacenter portfolio, raising operational maturity as cloud demand accelerated.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Microsoft &mdash; Senior Operations Program Manager, Datacenter Strategy, Automation &amp; Manageability</h2>
    <p class="muted">Apr 2011 – Jan 2013 · Redmond, WA</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Contributed to standardizing global datacenter automation platforms.</li>
      <li>Helped define scope and roadmap for Azure datacenter tooling initiatives.</li>
      <li>Supported transition of datacenter operations into service engineering organizations.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>TEKsystems (Microsoft Engagement) &mdash; IT Operations Program Manager</h2>
    <p class="muted">Nov 2010 – Mar 2011 · Redmond, WA</p>
    <p>
      Supported Microsoft Online Services operations during platform transitions, focusing on operational readiness
      and service support.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Tata Consultancy Services &mdash; Service Delivery Owner / Operations Program Manager (Microsoft Engagement)</h2>
    <p class="muted">May 2005 – Oct 2010 · India &amp; Redmond, WA</p>
    <p>
      Served as Service Delivery Owner and Operations Program Manager for Microsoft Online Services as part of TCS's
      Microsoft engagement, supporting platforms including Windows Mobile, Windows Live Voice &amp; Video, Live Call,
      SMS Messenger, MSN Alerts, Skybox, and Marketplace.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Owned end-to-end datacenter operations and service delivery, ensuring availability, operational readiness, and SLA compliance.</li>
      <li>Led regional infrastructure and operations teams across Europe and India.</li>
      <li>Partnered closely with Microsoft engineering and operations stakeholders to support large-scale, customer-facing services.</li>
      <li>Strengthened incident response, operational processes, and service reliability across managed platforms.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

